Package: vastR
Title: Visual Argument Structure Tool for R
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Luebber", "Finn", email = "f.luebber2@uni-luebeck.de",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0893-2120"))
    )
Description: An R implementation of the Visual Argument Structure Tool (VAST)
    introduced by Leising, Grenke, and Cramer (2023). VAST provides a visual
    language for mapping argument structures, distinguishing between concepts,
    their names, different types of relationships (causation, implication,
    prediction, transformation, reasoning), beliefs about what IS or OUGHT to
    be the case, and different perspectives on these beliefs. This package
    generates Graphviz DOT code and renders diagrams via 'DiagrammeR'.
Status: experimental
